formula: // This is a calculated field
// It transforms time in seconds into DD:HH:MM:SS format
STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])/86400)) 
 
+ " day(s) " + 
 
IF (INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%86400/3600)) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%86400/3600))
 
+ ":" + 
 
IF INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%3600/60) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%3600/60)) 
 
 
+ ":" + 
 
IF INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)]) %3600 %60) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)]) %3600 %60))

com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.ViewPr.viewLogic:
SELECT
	customer.customer_id,
	first_name,
	last_name,
	amount,
	payment_date,
	rental_id
FROM
	customer
INNER JOIN payment 
    ON payment.customer_id = customer.customer_id
where customer.customer_id = <[Parameters].[Parameter 1]>
ORDER BY payment_date

SELECT
	c.customer_id,
	c.first_name customer_first_name,
	c.last_name customer_last_name,
	s.first_name staff_first_name,
	s.last_name staff_last_name,
	amount,
	payment_date
FROM
	customer c
INNER JOIN payment p 
    ON p.customer_id = c.customer_id
INNER JOIN staff s 
    ON p.staff_id = s.staff_id
ORDER BY payment_date

com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.ViewPr.viewLogic:
SELECT
	customer.customer_id,
	first_name,
	last_name,
	amount,
	payment_date,
	rental_id
FROM
	customer
INNER JOIN payment 
    ON payment.customer_id = customer.customer_id
where customer.customer_id = <[Parameters].[Parameter 1]>
ORDER BY payment_date

SELECT
	c.customer_id,
	c.first_name customer_first_name,
	c.last_name customer_last_name,
	s.first_name staff_first_name,
	s.last_name staff_last_name,
	amount,
	payment_date
FROM
	customer c
INNER JOIN payment p 
    ON p.customer_id = c.customer_id
INNER JOIN staff s 
    ON p.staff_id = s.staff_id
ORDER BY payment_date
